author: Dave DeLuca (david.deluca@performgroup.com)
title: Former Raiders, Dolphins defensive end Quentin Moses dies in house fire
text:
Former Dolphins defensive end Quentin Moses was one of three people who died in a Georgia house fire early Sunday morning. 
Moses, 33, was found unconscious in the house and was later pronounced dead at Clearview Medical Center, according to the Atlanta Journal-Constitution . Andria Godard, 31, and her 10-year-old daughter Jasmine Godard were also found dead inside the Monroe, Ga. home. 
MORE: Notable sports deaths of 2017 
Moses played for the Georgia Bulldogs from 2003-06 before being selected in the third round of the 2007 NFL Draft by the Raiders. He failed to make the team's 53-man roster and was cut by former Raiders coach Lane Kiffin just before the regular season. He spent the next four seasons with the Dolphins, where he had 3.5 sacks in 44 games. 
Moses had been serving as a defensive line coach at Reinhardt University in Waleska, Ga. since leaving the Dolphins in 2011. Watch This
